⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Kraid
node MET · MET · ⟦Kraid:MET:712cf7⟧

WHO   — Kraid — the beast of Brinstar
WHAT  — A boss of the original Metroid, returned in Super Metroid as a colossal creature who fills the entire screen — hurling its claws and belly-spikes at the hunter who dares descend.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Mother Brain set her beasts to guard the way; because Brinstar is his lair and his dominion; and because anything that enters the depths is prey to be torn apart and turned back.
HOW   — By sheer size and reptilian fury — by flinging spikes from his belly, lashing with clawed talons, and spitting projectiles from his maw, a wall of living muscle barring the path deeper into Zebes.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the beast of Brinstar — I fill the cavern, and my belly is a wall of spikes; come no deeper.

spoken token : kul-kum-zeik   ·   hex : 712cf7
